                                           String Class
                                           
String are sequence of character. String are treated as object.
String class are immutable, so that once it is created a sring object cannot be changed.
If there is a necessity to make a lot of modifications to Strings of characters, then you should
 use String Buffer & String Builder-
 
 what is StringBuffer and StringBuilder----
 
                StringBuffer                                              StringBuilder
 1) Thread safe and synchronised                            1) not thread safe (not snchronised)
 2) introduced in java 1.0                                  2) introduced in java 1.5
 3) if the thred saftey is nessesry the                     3) faster than StringBuffer
    best option is StringBuffer